         <abstract>
            <p>We develop a new approach, the method of wavewise entropy inequalities for the numerical analysis of hyperbolic conservation laws. The method is based on a new extremum tracking theory and Vol'pert's theory of BV solutions. The method yields a sharp convergence criterion which is used to prove the convergence of generalized MUSCL schemes and a class of schemes using flux limiters previously discussed in 1984 by Sweby.</p>
          </abstract>
